com.qualitestgroup.kdt.keywords.common

Class Database.ConnectionKeyword

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.qualitestgroup.kdt.framework.Keyword
      • com.qualitestgroup.kdt.keywords.common.Database.ConnectionKeyword
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    Database.MSInsertTest
    Enclosing class:
    Database

    public abstract static class Database.ConnectionKeyword
extends Keyword
    NOTE: This keyword is used as base for other keywords which desire database connectivity. It should not be used directly in the test file.

    Description: Abstract keyword that other keywords may use. This keyword manages connection state so that keywords which subclass it do not need to handle those details.

    Arguments:
    • ConnectionName: (Required) The name of the existing connection or new connection that is created
    • ConfigurationData: (Optional) The name of the configuration loaded from a LoadConfigurationData keyword invocation
    • CloseConnectionOnComplete: (Optional) If provided, will close connection in keyword cleanup
    • RollbackOnError: (Optional) If provided, will rollback the database transaction in keyword cleanup
    • Username: (Required if [ConfigurationData] not passed) Username to login with.
    • Password: (Required if [ConfigurationData] not passed) Password to login with.
    • Address: (Required if [ConfigurationData] not passed) Address to login with.
    • Type: (Required if [ConfigurationData] not passed) Type of database connection to use. Valid types are [Oracle, MSSQL, MSSQL-JTDS].
    • IntegratedSecurity: (Required if [ConfigurationData] not passed) Used for [MSSQL, MSSQL-JTDS] connections.
